  <constraints>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">BFF publish size MUST be ≤60 MB compressed. Verify before deploy. Current baseline ~43.88 MB.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §10">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o deploy/api-publish/` and verify compressed output size. Document in deploy memo.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Deploy in sequence (BFF first, then Code Pages). Do NOT parallelize — sequential is safer + each step's smoke can detect breakage before the next.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If ANY smoke fails, STOP. Document the failure. Do not continue with remaining deploys until operator triage.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Use the existing skills: `bff-deploy` for BFF, `code-page-deploy` for Code Pages.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">DO NOT push or deploy to prod / demo from this task. Dev environment only unless operator says otherwise.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">User confirmation required before each deploy step (operator visibility).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene: verify no new HIGH-severity CVEs from `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive`.</constraint>
  </constraints>

